---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Collins :: Digital Workbench">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-8">
    
    <section class="text-center my-16">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-purple-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent mb-6">
        Systems Explorer.
      </h1>
      
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        I'm a developer building a map of the web, from production backends to modern, local-first PWAs. This is my digital workbench.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-4 text-lg text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
      <p>
        My curiosity has always pushed me past the "how" and into the "why." I'm driven to understand the full system, not just a single part.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site archives that journey of exploration. It's not a gallery of "finished" products, but a ledger of experiments, "chain-reactions," and the key insights I've gathered while building with modern tools.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 flex justify-center gap-6">
      <a 
        href="/workbench" 
        class="text-lg font-semibold py-3 px-8 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full shadow-lg hover:shadow-blue-500/50 hover:scale-105 transition-all"
      >
        View My Workbench &rarr;
      </a>
      <a 
        href="/journey" 
        class="text-lg font-semibold py-3 px-8 bg-slate-200 text-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200 rounded-full hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-600 hover:scale-105 transition-all"
      >
        See My Learning Path
      </a>
    </div>

  </main>
</Layout>